<p>I was curious what counties and states are leading the way in COVID-19 vaccinations. I looked online and found a cool <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2020/us/covid-19-vaccine-doses.html" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">map from the NY Times</a> but nothing that gave me a quick overview. So, I created this table to list the most COVID-19 vaccinations by county &amp; state in order of the percentage vaccinated. This is the condensed version of the table, <a href="https://clintmcmahon.com/covid-19-vaccination-rates-by-county-state/">click here to view the full table</a>. The full table lists the percent for everyone in the county as well as 12+/18+/65+ years old.</p>

<p>The data comes from a .JSON file from <a href="https://github.com/mattwaite/cdc-county-vaccination-data" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">@mattwaite</a>‘s <a href="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mattwaite/cdc-county-vaccination-data/main/countyvaccinations.json" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">GitHub</a> repository.  That data is updated daily from the API that powers the <a href="https://covid.cdc.gov/covid-data-tracker/#county-view" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">CDC COVID Data Tracker</a> website. </p>

<p>From the CDC website, <strong>Completeness</strong> represents:</p>

<blockquote class="wp-block-quote"><p>Percent of [state]s fully vaccinated recipients with valid county of residence. States with lower percentages for valid county of residence should be interpreted with caution.</p><cite><a href="https://covid.cdc.gov/covid-data-tracker/#county-view" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">CDC COVID Data Tracker</a></cite></blockquote>
